Executive Profile
Sanjay   Khosla  Managing Director, New Zealand Milk LimitedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Mr. Sanjay Khosla served as an Executive Vice President of Mondelez International, Inc. (formerly, Kraft Foods Inc.) since January 2007 and served its President Developing Markets. Mr. Khosla served as the President of Developing Markets & Global Categories at Kraft Foods Inc. He served as an Executive Vice President of Kraft Foods Group, Inc. until September 30, 2012. He served as the President of Kraft International Commercial at Kraft Foods Inc. since January 22, ... 2007. Mr. Khosla served as the Managing Director of New Zealand Milk Ltd. (Alternate Name, Fonterra Brands Ltd.) of Fonterra Co-operative Group Ltd from 2004 to January 31, 2007. He has more than 35 years of international business experience from his career with food, beverage and consumer product leaders such as Mondelez, Kraft and Unilever. He also has animal health experience from his three-year tenure as Managing Director of Fonterra Brands and Food Service, a multi-national dairy cooperative based in New Zealand. He joined Kraft Foods in 2007. Mr. Khosla joined Fonterra Co-operative Group Ltd. in August 2004 following a 27-year career with Unilever based in India, London and Europe and culminating in positions as Senior Vice President Global Beverages and Chairman of the Board for the $5 billion Unilever beverages category. He manages a business that spans more than 40 countries. He jointly chaired Unilever Global Market Research Committee Superstar of the Year by New York publication Advertising Age. He developed Unilever's innovation system, which was adopted globally by NIIT Ltd. Mr. Khosla managed Unilever's beverages and culinary businesses in Central Asia and for five years based in London, he was responsible for the Pond's, Vaseline, Rexona and Axe brands. His work included the transformation of the Lipton tea business and the forging of a global joint venture with PepsiCo. He has been a Director of Blue Holdings GP, LLC since May 15, 2013. He has been Director of Iconix Brand Group, Inc. since September 27, 2016. He serves as a Director of 4C Insights, Inc. He has been a Director of Big Heart Pet Brands Corporation (formerly Del Monte Corporation) since May 2013. He has been a Non-Executive Independent Director of NIIT Ltd., since December 21, 2002. He has been an Independent Director of Zoetis Inc., since June 2013. He serves as a Trustee of the Goodman Theater in Chicago, IL, USA. Mr. Khosla served as a Director of Best Buy Co., Inc. from October 2008 to June 9, 2015. Mr. Khosla has an honours degree in Electrical Engineering from Indian Institute of Technology and completed Harvard University Advanced Management Programme in 1998.Read Full Background




