Sanjay Khosla


The Trust Project at Northwestern University
Contributors

























































Senior Fellow, Kellogg Markets and Customers Initiative (KMCI), Kellogg School of Management
Senior Advisor, Boston Consulting Group Kellogg School of Management / Consumer Products
Sanjay Khosla is a senior fellow in the Kellogg Markets and Customers Initiative and a senior advisor at the Boston Consulting Group. From 2007 to 2013, he was the president of developing markets at Kraft Foods (now Mondelez International), where he was responsible for several iconic brands. During his tenure, sales more than tripled, from $5 billion to $16 billion, and profitability and cash flow dramatically improved. Khosla is the co-author of Fewer Bigger Bolder (Portfolio, 2014) which offers a framework for achieving sustained, profitable growth.
















